				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ E_{{{\rm{ads}}}} = E_{{{\rm{total}}}} - E_{{{\rm{surface}}}} - E_{{{\rm{species}}}} $$\end{document}
in which the Etotal, Esurface and Especies are representative of the total energy of the adsorbed species with graphene surface, the energy of the empty graphene surface and the energy of the specific adsorbed species in the gas phase, respectively.
